"{\"uid\": \"americamagazine.org-politics-society-2024-08-06-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-last-supper-catholic-french-revolution\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"America Magazine  The Jesuit Review  It'sd\\u00e9j\\u00e0 vuall over again.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 63, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Or at least that's the way the French Olympic controversy feels.\", \"from\": 64, \"to\": 128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 95, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cultural elites mocking Christian symbols?\", \"from\": 129, \"to\": 171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 153, \"end\": 162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998857865714, \"rank\": 1.1421299386665172e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In France?Sacr\\u00e9bleu!How did they come up with something so original?\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 240, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Drag queens?\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 253, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How transgressive!\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only the flabby Smurf was new.\", \"from\": 273, \"to\": 303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My first reaction to the silhouette of Da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper\\\" filled in with a tableau of bacchanalia was, I will admit, a yawn.\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 344, \"end\": 352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6118902173866747e-45, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's only been a few months since transgender activistsused St. Patrick's Cathedral as the backdrop for another vulgar show; the National Endowment for the Arts once funded a photo ofa crucifix submerged in urine; I have seen Jesus depicted as a bare-chested woman named \\\"Christa.\\\"\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 504, \"end\": 511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.491130614378979e-13, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\"}, {\"begin\": 666, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.35150515015332e-16, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yadda, yadda, yadda.\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 742, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is not there a Marvel remake to watch instead?\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Fast and Furious 86\\\"?\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anything more creative?\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not, however, another column tut-tutting at the Catholic League for taking the stale bait.\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 898, \"end\": 913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/War_of_the_League_of_Cambrai\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3472395595616764e-19, \"text\": \"Catholic League\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/War_of_the_League_of_Cambrai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/War_of_the_League_of_Cambrai\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lighten up!\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dialogue!\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 962, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Put it in context!\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is an admission that I ought to be more offended than I am.\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 1047, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In this case, history and context make the display more insidious than the tit-for-tat provocations of the American political scene.\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1156, \"end\": 1164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985758096183, \"rank\": 1.4240102691983073e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Faithful Christians today in France are a minority, a minority that has even experiencedbloodshed.\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1191, \"end\": 1201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999983139019267, \"rank\": 1.653932277758887e-06, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1211, \"end\": 1217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French seminarians that I teach in Rome-among the most impressive national contingents-sometimes voice amazement to me at how freely Americans express religious ideas in public.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When France's President Emmanuel Macron ran into electoral trouble due to a high-handed governing style and policies that offended both right and left, he made a play for unity by pushing abortion and euthanasia.\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1675, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1468, \"end\": 1474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1487, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The unborn and the elderly-and those Christians who defend them-were a soft target, not able to put up much of a fight.\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1714, \"end\": 1724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999983139019267, \"rank\": 1.653932277758887e-06, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The display at the Olympics was not innocent fun gone too far or Europeans just being artsy-making boring movies with wan people staring into space.\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1945, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was bullying a minority.\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When it comes to religious liberty, France's modern record is darker than most Americans realize.\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2011, \"end\": 2017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Americans know that we had a revolution that won us independence from Britain and that one of the results of that revolution was a constitution guaranteeing the free exercise of religion.\", \"from\": 2073, \"to\": 2260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2143, \"end\": 2150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999889423635, \"rank\": 1.0096711024170735e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We know that France had a revolution not long after.\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2274, \"end\": 2280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Our flags are the same colors, and we assume that the results must have been about the same.\", \"from\": 2314, \"to\": 2406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Reading the great Soviet dissidentAleksandr Solzhenitsyn, however, helped me to appreciate the differences between the American War of Independence and the French Revolution.\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2426, \"end\": 2432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999999977599145, \"rank\": 2.236594519854331e-09, \"text\": \"Soviet\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In contemporary terms, ours was not a \\\"revolution\\\" so much as a colonial independence movement.\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2678, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the historian Nathaniel Philbrick writes, describing Boston's patriots before Lexington and Concord, they \\\"were not trying to reinvent the world as they then knew it; they were attempting to get back to the way it had been when they were free from imperial restraint.\\\"\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2696, \"end\": 2715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathaniel_Philbrick\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nathaniel Philbrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathaniel_Philbrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathaniel_Philbrick\"}, {\"begin\": 2735, \"end\": 2741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.624506153162083e-27, \"text\": \"Boston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\"}, {\"begin\": 2760, \"end\": 2769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lexington_Avenue\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.4382900585283635e-24, \"text\": \"Lexington\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lexington_Avenue\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lexington_Avenue\"}, {\"begin\": 2774, \"end\": 2781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concord_River\", \"score\": 0.8398660222143024, \"rank\": 0.19063628734602925, \"text\": \"Concord\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concord_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concord_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American colonists liked their way of life and were trying to preserve it from rule that had become, in their eyes, foreign and oppressive.\", \"from\": 2951, \"to\": 3094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2955, \"end\": 2963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985758096183, \"rank\": 1.4240102691983073e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French revolutionaries, on the other hand, were trying to destroy French society as they knew it and start over with something else.\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3100, \"end\": 3122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French revolutionaries\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\"}, {\"begin\": 3166, \"end\": 3172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bloodshed was in the revolution's DNA.\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whereas the American revolutionaries emphasized adherence to established legal principles-no taxation without representation, John Adams defending the Redcoats after the Boston Massacre-the first Bastille Day in France culminated with the extrajudicial beheading of the fortress's commander.\", \"from\": 3272, \"to\": 3563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3284, \"end\": 3308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Revolution\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8945089541442583e-63, \"text\": \"American revolutionaries\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Revolution\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Revolution\"}, {\"begin\": 3398, \"end\": 3408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Adams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.032469842733266e-54, \"text\": \"John Adams\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Adams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Adams\"}, {\"begin\": 3484, \"end\": 3490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic opening ceremony this year in Paris also featured a beheaded Marie Antoinette.\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3606, \"end\": 3611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.919286567889101e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3637, \"end\": 3653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3804042465334467e-55, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The choice struck me as a little odd, since, other than ISIS, regimes these days do not much advertise their beheadings.\", \"from\": 3655, \"to\": 3775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3711, \"end\": 3715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.519833590991655e-30, \"text\": \"ISIS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, hey,vive la r\\u00e9volution!\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 3804, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not to say that the American patriots were angels-as the loyalists could attest-but that the aims and self-understanding of the two \\\"revolutions\\\" were fundamentally at odds.\", \"from\": 3806, \"to\": 3987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3834, \"end\": 3851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriot_(American_Revolution)\", \"score\": 0.9999993611365647, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"American patriots\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriot_(American_Revolution)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriot_(American_Revolution)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nowhere are the differences more glaring than when it comes to religious liberty.\", \"from\": 3988, \"to\": 4069, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By and large, the American founding fathers-whatever their eclectic personal beliefs-saw religion as \\\"a necessary spring of popular government,\\\" as George Washington put it in his farewell address.\", \"from\": 4070, \"to\": 4267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4088, \"end\": 4096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985758096183, \"rank\": 1.4240102691983073e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4218, \"end\": 4235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.590673919595659e-26, \"text\": \"George Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American religious minorities, including Baptists and Catholics, supported the First Amendment precisely because they understood it to protect, not limit, the practice and expression of religion.\", \"from\": 4268, \"to\": 4463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4268, \"end\": 4276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985758096183, \"rank\": 1.4240102691983073e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4309, \"end\": 4317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baptists\", \"score\": 0.9999994253668606, \"rank\": 5.604771057129847e-07, \"text\": \"Baptists\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baptists\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baptists\"}, {\"begin\": 4322, \"end\": 4331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999997773620882, \"rank\": 2.2263822515540546e-07, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In France, by contrast, despite early support for moderate reforms among the clergy, the revolutionaries came to see Catholicism (rightly) as woven into the very fabric of French society-the society they aimed to destroy.\", \"from\": 4465, \"to\": 4686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4468, \"end\": 4474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 4637, \"end\": 4643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Revolution proceeded from mob violence to organized terror, it assumed ever more grandiose-indeed, messianic-pretensions.\", \"from\": 4687, \"to\": 4815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As Alexis de Tocquevilleobserveddecades later, the revolutionaries eventually saw themselves as ushering in the \\\"regeneration of the whole human race.\\\"\", \"from\": 4816, \"to\": 4967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The American understanding of religious liberty sees religious expression-while remaining neutral on most details-as a good.\", \"from\": 4969, \"to\": 5093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4973, \"end\": 4981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985758096183, \"rank\": 1.4240102691983073e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is concerned to protect religious minorities from state oppression, while the French revolutionary ethos eventually offered an alternative state religion and instituted an explicit program of \\\"dechristianization.\\\"\", \"from\": 5094, \"to\": 5310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5175, \"end\": 5181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The period that followed was among the most intense and brutal persecutions in the church's history.\", \"from\": 5312, \"to\": 5412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Worship and the celebration of the sacraments were forbidden and tens of thousands of Catholics killed.\", \"from\": 5413, \"to\": 5516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5499, \"end\": 5508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999997773620882, \"rank\": 2.2263822515540546e-07, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bloody persecution recurred during the reign of the Paris Commune, and the archbishop of Paris was executed in 1871.\", \"from\": 5517, \"to\": 5633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5606, \"end\": 5611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.919286567889101e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Napoleon allowed Catholics to worship but made sure the church was subordinated to the state.\", \"from\": 5634, \"to\": 5727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5634, \"end\": 5642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1618605022067214e-65, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}, {\"begin\": 5651, \"end\": 5660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999997773620882, \"rank\": 2.2263822515540546e-07, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French principle ofla\\u00efcit\\u00e9, in fact, gives a fancy name to low-level religious discrimination, institutionalizing bias against religious expression.\", \"from\": 5729, \"to\": 5881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5733, \"end\": 5739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Blasphemy-such as we saw at the Olympic opening ceremony-is allowed, but public expressions of faith are intolerable.\", \"from\": 5882, \"to\": 5999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An equally ugly icon of this instinct to discriminate was the scene of four armed French police officers standing over a Muslim woman andforcing her to remove her clothingon a beach in Nice-all facilitated by an irrational antipathy to faith masquerading as constitutional principle.\", \"from\": 6000, \"to\": 6283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6082, \"end\": 6095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.785354088255307e-41, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 6121, \"end\": 6127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9911769299370687, \"rank\": 0.008901609588093435, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the great ironies of the French Revolution has always been the way it was forced to ape the culture it sought to replace.\", \"from\": 6285, \"to\": 6413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The revolutionaries replaced the Gregorian calendar and made 1789 the new Year One.\", \"from\": 6414, \"to\": 6497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Revolutionary feast days (the Day of Genius!)\", \"from\": 6498, \"to\": 6543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"replaced Christmas and Easter.\", \"from\": 6544, \"to\": 6574, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like adolescents in a role-playing game, the revolutionaries came up with new religions-like Theophilanthropy-to go with their new holidays.\", \"from\": 6575, \"to\": 6715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They even added a cult of relics, parading the bones of Voltaire into Paris in solemn procession to be entombed in a former church.\", \"from\": 6716, \"to\": 6847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6772, \"end\": 6780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Voltaire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0445499977024917e-54, \"text\": \"Voltaire\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Voltaire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Voltaire\"}, {\"begin\": 6786, \"end\": 6791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.919286567889101e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Inventing a female figure to replace the Virgin Mary, they came up with\\u2026Marianne.\", \"from\": 6848, \"to\": 6929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6889, \"end\": 6900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999922865754, \"rank\": 7.713556110506025e-09, \"text\": \"Virgin Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 6920, \"end\": 6928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.728193324372034e-26, \"text\": \"Marianne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The revolutionaries, in other words, were forced to pirate the forms of a once-great Christian culture because they did not have enough cultural substance of their own for a truly creative endeavor.\", \"from\": 6931, \"to\": 7129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7016, \"end\": 7033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_culture\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_culture\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_culture\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French, after all, have a lot to be proud of culturally-from Chartres Cathedral to Mont Saint-Michel, from Joan of Arc to Th\\u00e9r\\u00e8se of Lisieux-but without Christianity, what's left to celebrate is rather less impressive (Foucault-really?).\", \"from\": 7133, \"to\": 7374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7137, \"end\": 7143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 7290, \"end\": 7302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999964384187, \"rank\": 3.5361413307920677e-09, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Years ago, when visiting Paris-as beautiful as its reputation is-I remember going to the Eiffel Tower and, when I got up close, thinking, \\\"It's impressive from a distance, but up close it's just a lot of steel girders and empty space.\\\"\", \"from\": 7375, \"to\": 7610, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What the organizers of the Paris Olympics put on display was their empty space-the vacuousness of the secular cultural project.\", \"from\": 7611, \"to\": 7738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end, that vacuousness is what makes the mockery of Christianity at the Paris Olympics so dull.\", \"from\": 7740, \"to\": 7841, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7798, \"end\": 7810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999964384187, \"rank\": 3.5361413307920677e-09, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even with all the resources at their disposal-mounds of corporate funds and French tax euros-all they could do was cannibalize Christian forms.\", \"from\": 7842, \"to\": 7985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7918, \"end\": 7924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 7969, \"end\": 7984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_ethics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian forms\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_ethics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_ethics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France did not put its best foot forward at the opening ceremony, and I am especially sorry for my French Catholic friends.\", \"from\": 7987, \"to\": 8110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7987, \"end\": 7993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 8086, \"end\": 8092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9180739254839347, \"rank\": 0.0831307815211176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 8093, \"end\": 8101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3061748155741023e-17, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's particularly nasty to beat up on a cultural minority at an event like the Olympics, and France's bishops are right to protest.\", \"from\": 8111, \"to\": 8242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8204, \"end\": 8210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9856134864341913, \"rank\": 0.014422354038414529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But whatever happens, I suspect I will probably doze through the closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 8243, \"to\": 8325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe they will use a guillotine to snuff out the Olympic flame.\", \"from\": 8326, \"to\": 8390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anthony R. Lusvardi, S.J., teaches sacramental theology at the Pontifical Gregorian University in Rome.\", \"from\": 8392, \"to\": 8495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8413, \"end\": 8417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Society_of_Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"S.J.\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Society_of_Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Society_of_Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 8455, \"end\": 8486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontifical_Gregorian_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pontifical Gregorian University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontifical_Gregorian_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontifical_Gregorian_University\"}, {\"begin\": 8466, \"end\": 8486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontifical_Gregorian_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gregorian University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontifical_Gregorian_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontifical_Gregorian_University\"}, {\"begin\": 8490, \"end\": 8494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\", \"score\": 0.9999940831551125, \"rank\": 4.479865380891051e-06, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the author of Baptism of Desire and Christian Salvation.\", \"from\": 8496, \"to\": 8558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8538, \"end\": 8557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salvation_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian Salvation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salvation_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salvation_in_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Catholic University of America Press, 2024)    Your source for jobs, books, retreats, and much more.\", \"from\": 8559, \"to\": 8660, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See all classifieds  Your daily guide to the most important stories from the Church and around the world - delivered to your inbox each morning.See more newsletters  Support a trusted Catholic voice at the intersection of the Church and the world.\", \"from\": 8662, \"to\": 8909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8846, \"end\": 8854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3061748155741023e-17, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Your daily guide to the most important stories from the Church and around the world - delivered to your inbox each morning.See more newsletters  LinkCopy link\", \"from\": 8911, \"to\": 9069, \"entities\": []}]}"